## Architecture Rules

- Preserve separation between transport, application logic, repositories, and infrastructure.
- Keep controllers/route handlers thin. Business rules → services; persistence → repositories.
- Cross-service calls must stay behind explicit shared clients, never raw HTTP from handlers.
- Microservices must not call each other synchronously for domain data; use events.
- The only exception is JWKS validation from `crm-auth`, which is a justified synchronous call.
- Security-sensitive behavior must prefer fail-fast validation over permissive defaults.
- All errors MUST be returned as `NormalizedError` (`code`, `message`, `details`, `traceId`, `correlationId`).

## Code Organization

```
src/
├── app.ts              — Hono app factory
├── server.ts           — HTTP server bootstrap
├── config/
│   └── env.ts          — Zod-validated environment
├── db/
│   ├── connection.ts   — Pool + Drizzle instance
│   ├── schema.ts       — Drizzle schema (all tables in schema_{{SERVICE_NAME}})
│   └── scripts/
│       ├── bootstrap.ts — Idempotent role/schema provisioning (superuser)
│       └── migrate.ts  — Drizzle migration runner
├── modules/
│   └── {domain}/       — Feature modules (router, service, repository, schemas)
├── shared/
│   ├── health.ts       — Health check utilities
│   ├── logger.ts       — Pino structured logger + AsyncLocalStorage trace
│   ├── redis.ts        — Redis connection factory
│   ├── worker-health.ts — Worker liveness file writer
│   └── middlewares/
│       ├── error-handler.middleware.ts  — Global onError → NormalizedError
│       └── request-logger.middleware.ts — traceId/correlationId injection
├── openapi/            — OpenAPI YAML and Swagger routes
└── workers/            — Background worker entrypoints
```

## Operational Rules

- Use `pnpm` only. Never add `npm` commands, lockfiles, or docs.
- `pnpm db:bootstrap` must be idempotent and safe to rerun without affecting other services.
- Background workers expose liveness via `/tmp/worker-healthy` (written by `startWorkerHealthcheck`).
- Workers must handle `SIGTERM` gracefully (finish current message, then exit).
- Never commit real credentials, private keys, or secret material.

## Development Rules

- Keep documentation minimal: only `README.md` and this file.
- All new endpoints must be added to `gateway/gateway.manifest.json` and `openapi/openapi.yaml`.
- Run `pnpm gateway:validate && pnpm openapi:check` before every PR.
